.el .ds Aq '
.TH media 1  "media " 
.SH NAME
media \- Media element control (list, play, pause, seek)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBmedia\fR [\fB\-\-frame\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Discover and control HTML5 audio and video elements on the current page. List all media elements with playback state, play/pause individual elements, seek to a specific time or to the end of the media. Supports targeting by index or CSS selector, bulk operations with \-\-all, and frame\-scoped media control with \-\-frame.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-frame\fR \fI<FRAME>\fR
Target frame by index, path (1/0), or \*(Aqauto\*(Aq
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
media\-list(1)
List all audio and video elements on the page
.TP
media\-play(1)
Play a media element
.TP
media\-pause(1)
Pause a media element
.TP
media\-seek(1)
Seek a media element to a specific time
.TP
media\-seek\-end(1)
Seek a media element to its end (duration)
.TP
media\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH EXTRA
EXAMPLES:
  # List all media elements on the page
  agentchrome media list

  # Play a media element by index
  agentchrome media play 0

  # Pause a media element
  agentchrome media pause 0

  # Seek to 15.5 seconds
  agentchrome media seek 0 15.5

  # Seek all media elements to end (skip narration gates)
  agentchrome media seek\-end \-\-all

  # List media elements inside an iframe
  agentchrome media \-\-frame 0 list

  # Play a media element by CSS selector
  agentchrome media play css:audio.narration
.SH CAPABILITIES
.PP
Media element control (list, play, pause, seek)
.TP
.B media list
List all audio and video elements on the page
.TP
.B media play
Play a media element
.TP
.B target
Media element index (from 'media list') or CSS selector (prefixed with 'css:')
.TP
.B --all
Apply to all media elements on the page
.TP
.B media pause
Pause a media element
.TP
.B target
Media element index (from 'media list') or CSS selector (prefixed with 'css:')
.TP
.B --all
Apply to all media elements on the page
.TP
.B media seek
Seek a media element to a specific time
.TP
.B target
Media element index or CSS selector (not required with --all)
.TP
.B time_pos
Time in seconds to seek to (positional for single target, --time for --all)
.TP
.B --all
Apply to all media elements on the page
.TP
.B --time
Time in seconds to seek to (use with --all)
.TP
.B media seek-end
Seek a media element to its end (duration)
.TP
.B target
Media element index (from 'media list') or CSS selector (prefixed with 'css:')
.TP
.B --all
Apply to all media elements on the page
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Examples:
.TP
.B \`agentchrome media list\`
List all audio and video elements on the page
.TP
.B \`agentchrome media play 0\`
Play the first media element
.TP
.B \`agentchrome media pause 0\`
Pause the first media element
.TP
.B \`agentchrome media seek 0 15.5\`
Seek a media element to 15.5 seconds
.TP
.B \`agentchrome media seek-end --all\`
Seek all media elements to end (skip narration gates)
.TP
.B \`agentchrome media --frame 0 list\`
List media elements inside a specific iframe
.TP
.B \`agentchrome media play css:audio.narration\`
Play a media element by CSS selector
